Subject: [R-jobs] Assistant Clinical Professor - University of Maryland
Message-ID: <CAHa6or1RqidgDrEoCni92TJ5YzVpLiEoPQfrBGSLMALeR0er3w@mail.gmail.com>

The University of Maryland?s University Honors program invites applications
for four faculty positions to begin in Fall 2020. Each of these Assistant
Clinical Professor positions offers a three-year, full-time appointment
with competitive salaries and generous benefits. These faculty positions
offer a rare opportunity to incubate and test innovative pedagogy,
co-design and independently teach creative new courses, mentor promising
and ambitious undergraduate students, all in the context of a thriving
living-learning community. At the heart of the program is an innovative,
multidisciplinary curriculum comprised of thematically organized courses on
topics of contemporary and enduring significance.

Candidates with expertise in data science, information science,
econometrics, and/or statistics  and interests in teaching undergraduate
honors are encouraged to apply for the theme ?Information and Power?, led
by faculty fellows James Archsmith and Lars Olson.  For more information
about the theme and the search please see:
https://www.universityhonors.umd.edu/acp.html.  An overview of University
Honors can be found here: https://www.universityhonors.umd.edu/overview.html.
The official job announcement is available at:
https://ejobs.umd.edu/postings/77675. For best consideration apply by
August 7, 2020.  A Ph.D or other terminal degree is required. Questions and
inquiries may be directed to Dr. Christine Jones at cjones46 at umd.edu.

